<paragraph blockId="9.[813,1455,1358,1409]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">
DISTRIBUTION. — 
<taxonomicName authority="Sanders &amp; Merle &amp; Puillandre, 2019" authorityName="Sanders &amp; Merle &amp; Puillandre" authorityYear="2019" box="[991,1068,1358,1382]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Olssonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[991,1068,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Olssonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1073,1138,1359,1383]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a genus restricted to the Eocene to early Miocene of 
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1057,1385,1408]" name="Peru" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="254" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[813,1456,1432,1589]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">DIAGNOSIS. — Shell biconic, dorsoventrally compressed, shortspired, with 7 primary cords on the convex part of the whorl, all but P1 evenly reduced in variceal and intervariceal intervals of each whorl (P1 hardly more expressed than other cords); posterior siphonal canal short; varices strictly aligned; prominent columellar callus.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[813,1456,1612,1848]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">
COMPARISONS. — 
<taxonomicName authority="Sanders &amp; Merle &amp; Puillandre, 2019" authorityName="Sanders &amp; Merle &amp; Puillandre" authorityYear="2019" box="[1012,1098,1612,1636]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Olssonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1012,1098,1612,1636]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Olssonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1107,1182,1613,1637]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1904" box="[1300,1411,1613,1636]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Marsupina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1300,1411,1613,1636]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Marsupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but possesses a lesser number of primary cords on the convex part of the whorl (
<quantity box="[956,998,1665,1689]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="Sanders &amp; Merle &amp; Puillandre, 2019" authorityName="Sanders &amp; Merle &amp; Puillandre" authorityYear="2019" box="[1005,1089,1665,1689]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Olssonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1005,1089,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Olssonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1097,1169,1666,1690]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<quantity box="[1182,1224,1665,1689]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1904" box="[1231,1340,1666,1689]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Marsupina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1231,1340,1666,1689]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Marsupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1853" box="[861,908,1692,1715]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Aspa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[861,908,1692,1715]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Aspa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has a much more prominent columellar callus, it is much more granulose, and it has a more sharply defined shoulder and a wider spire angle. 
<taxonomicName authority="Sanders &amp; Merle &amp; Puillandre, 2019" authorityName="Sanders &amp; Merle &amp; Puillandre" authorityYear="2019" box="[1182,1269,1745,1769]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Olssonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1182,1269,1745,1769]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Olssonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1278,1354,1745,1769]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble 
<taxonomicName box="[813,914,1771,1795]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" genus="Bufonaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,914,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Bufonaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[931,1011,1771,1795]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1699,1717]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[698,1267,754,1296]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 3. — Recent Bursidae: A, IM-2008-5350, Bursa condita (Gmelin,1791), « Nouvelle Calédonie », Jousseaume coll.; B, IM-2007-43072, Bufonaria perelegans Beu,1987,Santo Marine Biodiversity Survey 2006,Vanuatu;C, IM-2009-11906,Bursa corrugata (Perry,1811),Dakar’09,Senegal;D, IM-2007-43063,Tutufa rubeta (Linnaeus, 1758), Santo Marine Biodiversity Survey 2006, Vanuatu; E, IM-2007-40338, Bursa latitudo Garrard, 1961, Exploration de la Biodiversité et Isolement en mer du Corail,Nouvelle Calédonie;F, IM-2009-5150, Lampadopsis rhodostoma (G.B. Sowerby II, 1835), MAINBAZA,Mozambique channel; G, IM-2009-5148, Bursa granularis (Röding, 1798), juvenile, MAINBAZA, Mozambique channel; H, IM-2009-11653, Bursa quirihorai Beu, 1987, Exploration de la Biodiversité et Isolement en mer du Corail, New Caledonia. All are ventral views. Scale bars: A-D, 2 cm; E-H, 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
), with the same straight anterior siphonal canal, but lacks a spine or blade on the posterior siphonal canal (
<figureCitation box="[821,899,1824,1848]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1699,1717]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[698,1267,754,1296]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 3. — Recent Bursidae: A, IM-2008-5350, Bursa condita (Gmelin,1791), « Nouvelle Calédonie », Jousseaume coll.; B, IM-2007-43072, Bufonaria perelegans Beu,1987,Santo Marine Biodiversity Survey 2006,Vanuatu;C, IM-2009-11906,Bursa corrugata (Perry,1811),Dakar’09,Senegal;D, IM-2007-43063,Tutufa rubeta (Linnaeus, 1758), Santo Marine Biodiversity Survey 2006, Vanuatu; E, IM-2007-40338, Bursa latitudo Garrard, 1961, Exploration de la Biodiversité et Isolement en mer du Corail,Nouvelle Calédonie;F, IM-2009-5150, Lampadopsis rhodostoma (G.B. Sowerby II, 1835), MAINBAZA,Mozambique channel; G, IM-2009-5148, Bursa granularis (Röding, 1798), juvenile, MAINBAZA, Mozambique channel; H, IM-2009-11653, Bursa quirihorai Beu, 1987, Exploration de la Biodiversité et Isolement en mer du Corail, New Caledonia. All are ventral views. Scale bars: A-D, 2 cm; E-H, 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
; white arrow).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="254" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[813,1455,1907,2029]" box="[813,913,1907,1933]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[813,1455,1907,2029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="254">
The representatives of this genus are the oldest confirmed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1925" box="[813,914,1971,1997]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Bursidae</taxonomicName>
; as such they can be used to calibrate the node 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1925" box="[813,914,2003,2029]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bursidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="254" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Bursidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
